layerWindow<br>-search for Gauge item=&quot;Player_HP&quot;; go down to TestOffsetX; replace the number there by -250 (or 250 if you have a loooooong surname)<br><br><br>Slightly off topic, but worth mentioning anyway:<br><br>+Keep your window positions when loading a new skin<br>-in EQ, type loadskin whatever 1<br><br>Grygan<br>Barbecue Grandmaster <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugrygan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grygan</A> at: 8/1/02 7:08:42 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uguice666.showPublicProfile?language=EN>guice666</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Posts: 1961<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/31/02 6:49:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=137.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.gpcentre.net/images/gerbil.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A simple tweaking guide for your xml files...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> +Remove the name from the PlayerWindow<br>-search for Gauge item=&quot;Player_HP&quot;; go down to TestOffsetX; replace the number there by -250</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>I would suggest pushing it down rather than up. That way you don't get any surname suprises, like I did. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I put my Text Offset to 30, pushing it below the 8 pixels I give way for the bar itself.<br> <p><LINK REL=STYLESHEET TYPE="text/css" HREF="http://www.gpcentre.net/style.css" TITLE="Cool"><P><DIV ALIGN=CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=2 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=90%>   <TR>      <TD COLSPAN=4 ALIGN=CENTER style="font-weight: bold">This game has warped my fragile little mind.</td></tr>  